snippet: Francis Keenan, 28, and Jarod Von Rueden, 22, were trying to scale Mount Aconcagua when Mr. Von Rueden sent out a distress radio signal Dec. 31.
abstract: Argentinian officials say two bodies discovered at the bottom of a 650-foot ravine on a mountain are believed to be those of Francis Keenan and Jarod Von Rueden, two missing American climbers.
lead_paragraph: Francis Keenan, 28, and Jarod Von Rueden, 22, were trying to scale Mount Aconcagua when Mr. Von Rueden sent out a distress radio signal Dec. 31.

headline.main: Bodies of 2 American Climbers Found in Argentina
headline.print_headline: Bodies of 2 Climbers Found in Argentina
